[color=#40BF00][size=150]User-defined bindings[/size][/color]

For creating bindings, you need to place [c]<FILE>.JSON (UTF-8)[/c] in “[c]DSLKeyPad\User\profile-<PROFILE>\CustomBindings\[/c]” with the same structure:


[spoiler2="Details"]

[code=json]
{
  "info": {
    // Preset name
    "name": "Esoteric Binds"
  },
  // Lists of binds, as for single keys
  // and for keys with modifier keys
  "binds": {
    "2:LangFlat": ["digit_2::superscript×20", "digit_1::superscript×10"],
    "A": ["alchemical_brimstone", "alchemical_brimstone_philosophers"],
    "<^>!A": "alchemical_brimstone_black",
    "<^>!B": ["astrological_proserpina"],
    ">+A:Caps": ["astrological_neptune", "astrological_uranus"],
    "<^>!И": ["astrological_chiron"],
    "<^>!Y": [
      "@ඞʂ🍋",
      "@Сижу за решёткой в темнице сырой.\nВскормленный в неволе орёл молодой,\n…"
    ]
  }
}
[/code]

	User-defined bindings supports the following formats:

[code=json]
		// “Flat” (for all languages)
		<"MODIFIER?KEY">: <"VAL">
		// For a specific language
		<"MODIFIER?KEY">: [<"VAL">]
		// Same as above, but different values for active and inactive CapsLock
		<"MODIFIER?KEY">: [<"VAL">, <"VAL">]
		// “Flat” variant
		<"MODIFIER?KEY:Caps">: [<"VAL">, <"VAL">]
		// Binding where the first variant will refer to the English keyboard layout,
		// and the second to the Russian one
		<"MODIFIER?KEY:LangFlat">: [<"VAL">, <"VAL">]
[/code]

And the following values:

[code=json]
		// Just text
		"@<TEXT>"
		// Reference to an entry in the library
		"<ENTRY NAME>::<VARIANT>×<COUNT>"
[/code]

Details about reference format see in the “Reference format” section.

[b]Note:[/b] for [c]RAlt[/c] you need to use [c]<^>![/c].

After creating a preset, it can be selected in the settings window or after restarting the program, or after pressing the 🔁 button next to the dropdown list in the settings window.

[hr]

[/spoiler2]



[color=#40BF00][size=150]User-defined sequences[/size][/color]

You can create/edit custom sequences, called “My Recipes”, in the same way as for bindings or with a dedicated recipe-creation GUI. Custom recipes may contain large multiline text as a result.


[spoiler2="Details"]

The main file is presented in JSON format, “[c]DSLKeyPad\User\profile-<PROFILE>\CustomRecipes.json[/c]”. You can also add additional recipe files in INI (UTF-16 LE) or JSON (UTF-8) formats by placing them in the “[c]DSLKeyPad\User\profile-<PROFILE>\CustomRecipes\[/c]” directory. Recipes from there will be automatically loaded at program startup or when pressing the refresh button in the “My Recipes” window.

Loading sequences from XCompose format files is supported. They must be placed in the “[c]DSLKeyPad\User\profile-<PROFILE>\XCompose\[/c]” directory. The file must end with the “[c].XCompose[/c]” extension.

[b]Note:[/b] Only simple XCompose sequences are supported, such as “[c]<Multi_key> <g> <r> <i> <n> : "😁"[/c]” or “[c]<Multi_key> <U1100> <U1100> : "ᄁ" U1101 # HANGUL CHOSEONG SSANGKIYEOK[/c]”. On first launch, for demonstration purposes, a “demo.XCompose” file is created at the specified path with the sequence “[c]<Multi_key> <0> <0> : "∞"[/c]”.

