[color=#40BF00][size=150]Reference format[/size][/color]

[c]${<ENTRY NAME>::<VARIANT>×<COUNT>}[/c] refers to an entry in the library if it exists.

With “[c]::[/c]” you can specify a “Glyph variant”, e.g.: [c]${digit_1}[/c] → “1”, then [c]${digit_1::superscript}[/c] → “¹”.

With “[c]×[/c]” at the end you can specify a number of repetitions, e.g. [c]${digit_1::superscript×10}[/c] → “¹¹¹¹¹¹¹¹¹¹”.

With “[c]\/[/c]” you can specify multiple entries by their full or partial names, e.g.: [c]${lat_c_let_\b,o,l,d/::bold}[/c] → 𝐁𝐎𝐋𝐃, [c]${\hel,lat/_c_let_a_alpha}[/c] → ΑⱭ, [c]${\nabla,delta,integral,square_root/}[/c] → ∇∆∫√.



[color=#40BF00][size=150]Alternative modes[/size][/color]

[b]Combination:[/b] [c]LWin + LAlt + S[/c] (selector)


[spoiler2="Details"]

[img]https://i.imgur.com/dqDd08b.png[/img]

Essentially — just sets of activated bindings for a whole list of writing systems/alphabets, mainly different from Latin and Cyrillic.

[b]Note:[/b] binding sets use Latin and Cyrillic keys, i.e. internal keyboard layout switching affects them. Incompatible with TELEX/VNI-like input modes.

Some writing systems are activated in pairs — one writing system works on the Latin layout, another on the Cyrillic layout. Otherwise, modes are [i]single[/i], work on several language layouts at once, but are designed specifically for Latin (especially modes with syllable input).


[list=1]
[*][b][url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greek_alphabet]Hellenic script[/url][/b] (also known as [i]Greek[/i]) — allows entering both symbols of the modern Greek alphabet and ancient Greek signs with the addition of various other symbols related to it, for example:
αάὰὰἀᾳᾱᾰἅἄἃἂἇἆ ΐ ϐϕϱϖϰϲϵ
· ; ⸒ ⸏ ⸐ ⸑ ⸎ ⸔ ⸕ ⸓ ⸖ ʹ ͵ ₯

It differs from the standard Greek layout by the typical English arrangement of non-letter symbols and the presence of [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koppa_(letter)]koppa[/url] and [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digamma]digamma[/url] ([c]Ϟ[/c] [c]Ϝ[/c]) in place of [c]Q[/c] [c]W[/c] ([c];[/c] [c]ς[/c] on the Greek layout). Here the [c]ς[/c] sign is entered by the combination [c]LAlt Σ (S)[/c].

The position of bindings does not change when switching Latin/Cyrillic layouts — a separate layout has been introduced for Hellenic script, however it cannot be changed (well, it can, I just didn’t consider it necessary to add a selection item in the GUI settings).

[*][b][url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Runes]Germanic runes[/url][/b] — allows entering [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Runes]runes[/url] of the Elder Futhark, Anglo-Saxon Futhorc, Younger Futhark, Medieval runes, “Golden numbers” 17–19 of the Runic almanac (ᛮᛯᛰ), Runes from the [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franks_Casket]Franks Casket[/url] and three more [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cirth#Unicode]Tolkien runes[/url] for company. Plus punctuation marks (᛫᛬᛭).

[*][b][url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glagolitic_script]Glagolitic[/url][/b] — based on the Cyrillic layout and allows entering both simple Glagolitic letters and combinable ones with corresponding diacritics. Activated in pair with “Germanic runes”.

[*]And others, already indicated in the screenshot writing systems and alphabets: [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Turkic_script]Old Turkic script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Permic_script]Old Permic script[/url] (Cyrillic layout, paired with Old Turkic), [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Szekely_script]Székely script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gothic_alphabet]Gothic script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Etruscan_alphabet]Etruscan script[/url] ([i]Old Italic[/i], includes symbols not only from the Etruscan alphabet), [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoenician_alphabet]Phoenician script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_South_Arabian_script]South Arabian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_North_Arabian]North Arabian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carian_alphabets]Carian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lycian_alphabet]Lycian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lydian_alphabet]Lydian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidetic_language]Sidetic script[/url] (currently the mode and symbol library entries are introduced, but officially Sidetic script will be introduced in Unicode with the release of Unicode 17.0 on September 9th at minimum, so there will be squares instead of letters for now and fonts cannot be found), [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cypriot_syllabary]Cypriot syllabic script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tifinagh]Tifinagh[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ugaritic_alphabet]Ugaritic script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Persian_cuneiform]Old Persian script[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet]International Phonetic Alphabet[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deseret_alphabet]Deseret alphabet[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shavian_alphabet]Shavian alphabet[/url] and a mode for entering mathematical symbols.
[/list]

I don’t guarantee full coverage for each mode, but upon discovering new or missed symbols — the mode will be supplemented.

