[/spoiler2]



[color=#40BF00][size=150]TELEX/VNI-like Input[/size][/color]

[b]Combinations:[/b] [c]RAlt + F2[/c] (Vietnamese), [c]RAlt + RShift + F2[/c] (PinYin) / [c]LWin + LAlt + D[/c] (selector)


[spoiler2="Details"]

[img]https://i.imgur.com/bKeoDzy.png[/img]

Modes based on Vietnamese [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telex_(input_method)]TELEX[/url] and [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VNI]VNI[/url] layouts to facilitate input of Vietnamese (with the addition of letters from the [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jarai_language]Jarai alphabet[/url]) and [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinyin]PinYin[/url]. Incompatible with Alternative Input modes.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DemerNkardaz/DSL-KeyPad-Docs/refs/heads/main/Media/telex_demo.gif[/img]

To enter letters with diacritics, you need to enter a sequence of characters, for example: [c]AWS[/c] → Ắ (A → Ă → Ắ), [c]A5[/c] → Ẫ, [c]DD[/c]→ Đ, [c]BB[/c] → Ƀ, [c]UONGW[/c] → ƯƠNG, [c]UONG5[/c] → ƯỠNG. To cancel sequence combining, you can use [c]\[/c], [c]A\W[/c] → AW instead of Ă or re-enter the last character (AW → ĂW → AW). The last entered diacritic can be canceled by entering Z (ǕZ → ÜZ → U).

You can change the diacritic of an already entered character if you don’t move the cursor: [c]ẰS[/c] → Ắ, [c]ẮA[/c] → Ấ, [c]ẤJ[/c] → Ậ, [c]ẬR[/c] → Ẩ…

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DemerNkardaz/DSL-KeyPad-Docs/refs/heads/main/Media/telex_switch_demo.gif[/img]

