[b]Temperature Converter[/b]

Works through auto-replacement strings, requiring text input in the format [c]\tcalc{<FROM><TO>}[/c] (for example, [c]\tcalc{cf}[/c] = from ℃ to ℉). After triggering, value input for conversion is activated, and pressing any key that is not a digit, comma, period, or “'” confirms the output of the converted value to the input field.

The following scales are available: Celsius (C), Fahrenheit (F), Kelvin (K), [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delisle_scale]Delisle (D)[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leiden_scale]Leiden (L)[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton_scale]Newton (N)[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wedgwood_scale]Wedgwood (W)[/url] (revised), [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rankine_scale]Rankine (Ra)[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R%C3%A9aumur_scale]Réaumur (Re)[/url], [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R%C3%B8mer_scale]Rømer (Ro)[/url], Dalton (Da).

When specifying a fractional part, you can choose the output format (the fractional part value can be omitted — “450,”):

[list]
[*]<Integer>.<Fractional> → 999,727.59 ℃
[*]<Integer>,<Fractional> → 999 727,59 ℃
[*]<Integer>.,<Fractional> → 999.727,59 ℃
[*]<Integer>..<Fractional> → 999 727.59 ℃
[*]<Integer>'<Fractional> → 999’727.59 ℃
[*]<Integer>''<Fractional> → 999’727,59 ℃
[/list]

[hr]

[b]LaTeX → Symbol[/b]

Auto-replacement strings in the format [c]$><LaTeX-command>$[/c]. If any LaTeX command is registered in the library, then the symbol associated with it can be entered this way as well, examples: [c]$>\AE$[/c] → Æ, [c]$>\={\AE}$[/c] → Ǣ, [c]$>\Omega$[/c] → Ω, [c]$>\textpertenthousand$[/c] → ‱.

[hr]

[b]URL Encoding String[/b]

Combinations: (select text) → [c]RCtrl \[/c] (encode), [c]RLCtrls \[/c] (decode).

Not my own logic, found on the [url=https://www.autohotkey.com/boards/viewtopic.php?p=554647&sid=83cf90bcab788e19e2aacfaa0e9e57e3#p554647]AHK forum[/url].

Converts string to URL encoding and back: [c]Something[/c] ↔ [c]%53%6F%6D%65%74%68%69%6E%67[/c], [c]𐌲𐍉𐌸[/c] ↔ [c]%F0%90%8C%B2%F0%90%8D%89%F0%90%8C%B8[/c].

[hr]

[b]Enclose in Quotes[/b]

Combination: (select text) → [c]LAlt + 2[/c]

Encloses selected text in quotes and automatically replaces outer quotes with inner ones if they exist: Меч Танаквиль → Меч «Танаквиль» → «Меч „Танаквиль“», Sword Tanaquil → Sword “Tanaquil” → “Sword ‘Tanaquil’”

Quotes are chosen depending on the active keyboard layout language, also works for Greek (both for the layout and for the Alternative “Hellenic script” mode): Ξίφος Τανακυλλίς → Ξίφος «Τανακυλλίς» → «Ξίφος “Τανακυλλίς”».

[hr]

[b]Open Web Page of Selected Symbol[/b]

Combination: (select text) → [c]LWin + LAlt + PgUp[/c]

Simply opens the page of the selected symbol on the Unicode resource chosen in settings.

